Summary.

(Updated Apr.4.2018 1pm PST)

The purpose of this PR is to enable existing Three.js core to run with WebGL 2.0 + to enable users to run their GLSL ES 3.00 shader code without any exposed API changes. New WebGL 2.0 features should be added in another PR, not in this PR.

Changes are:

**~Add `webglVersion` option to `WebGLRenderer` constructor.~**

~`webglVersion` specifies which version of `WebGLContext` will be created~
- ~'webgl': webgl1~
- ~'webgl2': webgl2~
- ~'auto': try webgl2 or fallback to webgl1~
- ~undefined: right now acts as 'webgl', once Three.js + WebGL 2.0 becomes stable acts as 'auto' (See https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/pull/13701#issuecomment-377009238)~

We don't wanna introduce new API we need to maintain forever. We require Users to create webgl2 context by themselves and pass to `WebGLRenderer` constructor so far.

    var canvas = document.createElement( 'canvas' );
    var context = canvas.getContext( 'webgl2' );
    renderer = new WebGLRenderer( { canvas: canvas, context: context } );

I guess we switch to `WebGL2Context` as default once WebGL2.0 + Three.js becomes stable.

**Save `isWebGL2` to WebGL(2)Context.**

`WebGLRenderer` saves `.isWebGL2` to the context when it creates the context. Other modules can check if the context is WebGL 2.0 with `if ( gl.isWebGL2 )`. Pros: we don't have duplicated check logic across modules, Cons: polluting WebGL(2)Context.

Another option is to have `.isWebGL2( gl )` function in utils.js or somewhere?

**Convert GLSL 1 to 3 for WebGL 2.0 runtime.** 

I wanna suggest GLSL 3 should always be used for WebGL 2.0 because some WebGL 2.0 features expects GLSL3, for example UBO. And for the simplicity I don't wanna think the combination of WebGL 2.0 + GLSL 1.

The current shader code is GLSL 1. To share the shader code between WebGL 1.0 and 2.0 `WebGLProgram` attempts to convert GLSL1 to 3 runtime with `#define` macros.

Related, converting GLSL 3 to 1 approach #13701

**Allow GLSL 3 user shader code.**

Users can write their user GLSL 3 shader code with `(Raw)ShaderMaterial` by adding `#version 300 es` in the head

    #version 300 es

    out highp vec4 glFragColor;
    void main() {
        glFragColor = vec4( 1.0 );
    }

**Update extension handling for WebGL 2.0.**

Some extensions for WebGL 1.0 became built-in features in WebGL 2.0, for example ANGLE_instanced_arrays extension. So we need to update extension handling for such extensions.

The code in modules which use such extensions checks if the context is WebGL 2.0

    if ( gl.isWebGL2 ) {

        gl.something();

    } else {

        var extension = extensions.get( 'something' );
        if ( extension !== null ) extension.something_EXT();

    }

**Update Texture internalFormat handling for WebGL 2.0.**

In WebGL 2.0, InternalFormat/Format/Type combination for texImage2D should be one of the combinations listed in 

https://www.khronos.org/registry/webgl/specs/latest/2.0/#TEXTURE_TYPES_FORMATS_FROM_DOM_ELEMENTS_TABLE

`WebGLTextures` attempts to choose appropriate InternalFormat for WebGL 2.0.

**No force POT.**

WebGL 2.0 doesn't require POT texture.

**Add `Detector.webgl2`.**

Users can check if browser seems to support WebGL 2.0 with `Detector.webgl2`.

hello for full shader conversion to webgl2, add this to WebGLShader ( bool gl.v2 = true )
```javascript
function WebGLShader( gl, type, string ) {

    if ( gl.v2 !== undefined ) {

        if ( type === gl.VERTEX_SHADER ) {
        	string = "#version 300 es\n" + string;
			string = string.replace(/attribute /g, "in ");
			string = string.replace(/varying /g, "out ");
			string = string.replace(/transpose/g, "transposition");
        } else {
        	string = "#version 300 es\n" + string;
			string = string.replace("uniform vec3 cameraPosition;", "uniform vec3 cameraPosition;\nout vec4 FragColor_gl;\n");
			string = string.replace("#extension GL_OES_standard_derivatives : enable", "");
			string = string.replace(/varying /g, "in ");
			string = string.replace(/transpose/g, "transposition");
			string = string.replace(/gl_FragColor/g, "FragColor_gl");
			string = string.replace(/texture2D/g, "texture");
			string = string.replace(/textureCube/g, "texture");
        }

    }

    var shader = gl.createShader( type );

    gl.shaderSource( shader, string );
    gl.compileShader( shader );

    ...
```

mm i think main problem's is image format internal and external is not same in gl2

```js
var iFormatPI2GL = function( format ){

    if( gl.v2 !== undefined ){

         if (format === me.TEXFMT.C4I8)  return { Format: gl.RGBA8,           External: gl.RGBA,             Type: gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C1I8)  return { Format: gl.R8,              External: gl.RED,              Type: gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C1F16) return { Format: gl.R16F,            External: gl.RED,              Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C4F16) return { Format: gl.RGBA16F,         External: gl.RGBA,             Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C1F32) return { Format: gl.R32F,            External: gl.RED,              Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C4F32) return { Format: gl.RGBA32F,         External: gl.RGBA,             Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.Z16)   return { Format: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT16, External: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT,  Type: gl.UNSIGNED_SHORT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.Z24)   return { Format: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT24, External: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT,  Type: gl.UNSIGNED_SHORT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.Z32)   return { Format: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT32F, External: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT,  Type: gl.UNSIGNED_SHORT }

    }else{
        
         if (format === me.TEXFMT.C4I8)  return { Format: gl.RGBA,            External: gl.RGBA,            Type: gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C1I8)  return { Format: gl.LUMINANCE,       External: gl.LUMINANCE,       Type: gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C1F16) return { Format: gl.LUMINANCE,       External: gl.LUMINANCE,       Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C4F16) return { Format: gl.RGBA,            External: gl.RGBA,            Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C1F32) return { Format: gl.LUMINANCE,       External: gl.RED,             Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.C4F32) return { Format: gl.RGBA,            External: gl.RGBA,            Type: gl.FLOAT }
    else if (format === me.TEXFMT.Z16)   return { Format: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT, External: gl.DEPTH_COMPONENT, Type: gl.UNSIGNED_SHORT }
    }

    return null;

}
```
